label.value: Agent Affecting Organs of Special Senses

value.value: An agent that exerts a physiologic effect on the organs of special senses, including the eyes, ears and nose. This category includes otic, nasal and ophthalmic agents.
An agent that exerts a physiologic effect on any anatomic entity that is part of the integumentary system, including skin, nails and hair.
Painful sensation in the external ear region.
A slight or incomplete paralysis of an extraocular muscle.
Painful sensation in the eye.
A disorder characterized by impaired eyelid function.
Swelling due to an excessive accumulation of fluid in facial tissues.

label.value: Stage I Ovarian Cancer AJCC v6 and v7

value.value: Stage I includes: T1, N0, M0. T1: Tumor limited to ovaries (one or both).  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 6th and 7th eds.)
A reduction in the strength of the facial muscles.
A reduction in the strength of the eye muscles.
Leakage due to breakdown of a fallopian tube anastomosis.
Blockage of the normal flow of the contents in the fallopian tube.
A rupture of the fallopian tube wall due to tubal pregnancy, or other traumatic or pathologic processes.
Narrowing of the lumen of the fallopian tube.
Fanconi Syndrome caused by exposure to noxious agents.
Shrinking of adipose tissue.
An abnormal communication between a female reproductive system organ and another organ or cavity.
The development of secondary female sex characteristics in males due to extrinsic factors.

Any substance that inhibits a protease, an enzyme that breaks peptide bonds. Proteases are required for many cell processes and inhibition of proteases can inhibit viral replication, inflammatory responses, proliferation, and tumor growth.

label.value: Stage II Ovarian Cancer AJCC v6 and v7

value.value: Stage II includes: T2, N0, M0.  T2: Tumor involves one or both ovaries with pelvic extension and/or implants.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 6th and 7th eds.)
A laboratory test result which indicates decreased levels of fibrinogen in a biological specimen.
Fibrotic degeneration of the deep connective tissues.
Complaints describing a pattern similar to influenza, which may include one or more of the following symptoms: fever, chills, muscle or body aches, cough, sore throat, rhinitis, or fatigue.
A finding referring to walking difficulties.
Painful sensation in the gallbladder region.
An abnormal communication between the gallbladder and another organ or cavity.
An acute or chronic infectious process affecting the gallbladder.
A necrotic process occurring in the gallbladder.
Blockage of the normal flow of the contents of the gallbladder.
A rupture in the gallbladder wall caused by traumatic or pathologic processes.

label.value: Stage III Ovarian Cancer AJCC v6 and v7

value.value: Stage III includes: T3, N0, M0.  T3: Tumor involves one or both ovaries with microscopically confirmed peritoneal metastasis outside pelvis.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 6th and 7th eds.)
Leakage due to breakdown of a gastric anastomosis.
An agent that promotes hemostasis.
An acute or chronic infectious process affecting the stomach.
An inflammatory process affecting the mucous membrane of the stomach.
A necrotic process affecting the gastric wall.
The political organization by which a nation, stateor region is ruled.
A rupture in the gastric wall caused by traumatic or pathologic processes.
Narrowing of the lumen of the stomach.
Leakage due to breakdown of a gastrointestinal anastomosis.
An abnormal communication between any part of the digestive system and another organ or cavity.

label.value: Stage IV Ovarian Cancer AJCC v6 and v7

value.value: Stage IV includes: Any T, Any N, M1.  M1: Distant metastasis (excludes peritoneal metastasis). (AJCC 6th and 7th eds.)
Painful sensation in the gastrointestinal region.
A necrotic process affecting the post-operative stoma area in the gastrointestinal tract.
any agent having a favorable effect on the function of the heart.
A reduction in the strength of muscles in multiple anatomic sites.
Swelling due to an excessive accumulation of fluid in the genitals.
Painful sensation in the gingival region.
A laboratory test result which indicates a decreased glomerular filtration rate.
A laboratory test result which indicates abnormal levels of growth hormone in a biologic specimen.
